Two ways to install DefaultTool-Changer:


 1. Use the Installerscript "Install"...

 2. Copy "DefaultTool-Changer" to the place to want.

    If the "reqtools.library" is not in LIBS:
    copy DefaultTool-Changer/Libs/reqtools.library to LIBS:

@EndNode
@Node "using" "DefaultTool-Changer/Using DefaultTool-Changer"
@Next "history"
@Prev "install"
@Toc  "Main"

Left part of the window:


 Listview "DefaultTools"  displays a list with old and new DefaultTools

                          Format:  old DefaultTool -> new DefaultTool

 Stringgadgets            left stringgadget:  old DefaultTool
                          right stringgadget: enter your new DefaultTool

                          copy an entry: press RETURN/ENTER in the right
                                         stringgadget at the end of your input

 "N"                      Activate the left stringgadget and you can enter a new entry

 "D"                      If "D" is selected all entries you select in the Listview
                          "DefaultTools" will deleted...


Right part of the window:

 "Clear List"              Clear the list with old/new DefaultTools

 "Examine Directory"       Scans the selected directory and add all new DefaultTools to
                           the Listview "Default-Tools"on the right part of the window.

 "Change DefaultTools"     Set the new DefaultTools for your selected directory.

                           If there is only an old DefaultTool and no new one the
                           DefaultTool from the icon(s) with this DefaultTool will
                           not changed.

 "Clean Up"                Deletes all entries with no new DefaultTool. You should
                           use this function before using "Change DefaultTools".
                           "Change DefaultTools" will be faster than witout "Clean Up".

 "Save List"               Save the list with the old/new DefaultTools to the file you want.

 "Load List"               Load a list from selected file...

 "Save Configuration"      Save window-size and window-position as tooltypes to your program-icon
                           and the program starts with this values next time...

 "Info"                    Requester with my address...

@EndNode
